# Commit message template for Claude-skills-research
# Usage: git config commit.template .git-commit-template
#
# Format: Type: Brief description (50 chars max for first line)
#
# Types:
# - Feature: New functionality or capability
# - Fix: Bug fix or correction
# - Update: Enhancement to existing feature
# - Refactor: Code restructuring without feature change
# - Docs: Documentation updates (README.md, CLAUDE.md, etc)
# - Test: Test additions or fixes
# - Chore: Maintenance, cleanup, dependencies
# - WIP: Work in progress (avoid for main branch)

# Example:
# Feature: Add Telnyx MCP server research capability
#
# Updates:
# - CLAUDE.md: Added new skill documentation
# - README.md: Updated getting started section
# - SKILL.md: Integrated new research methodology
#
# Key Changes:
# - 46-tool enumeration for Telnyx MCP
# - Security scoring (17/53 CCI)
# - Protocol version detection (FastMCP priority)
#
# Co-Authored-By: Claude Haiku 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

# IMPORTANT REMINDERS:
# 1. Always update CLAUDE.md for feature/fix changes
# 2. Always update README.md for release-level changes
# 3. Always update SKILL.md for methodology/learning changes
# 4. Include explicit list of files updated in commit message
# 5. Add Co-Authored-By line for all commits

# Commit to:
# - Include specific files changed in message
# - Reference version/release numbers for major changes
# - Link to relevant issues if applicable
